==English==
===Etymology===
From French ''[[némoral]]'' or Latin ''[[nemoralis]]'', from [[nemus]] ‘grove’.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈnɛmərəl/}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# Pertaining to [[grove]]s or [[woodland]].
#:*'''1974''': He drank his coffee standing in the clean wash of a wind '''nemoral''' and northern, its light going thin and cold. — Guy Davenport, ''Tatlin!''

